  "instructions": [
    "Preheat the oven to 400°F (200°C).",
    "Heat 2 tablespoons of coconut oil in a large Dutch oven over medium-high heat.",
    "Add the chicken thighs and cook until browned on all sides, about 5-7 minutes per side.",
    "Remove the chicken from the pot and set it aside.",
    "Add the mixed bell peppers and onions to the pot and cook until they start to soften, about 5 minutes.",
    "Add the garlic, ginger, cumin, smoked paprika, cayenne pepper, salt, and pepper to the pot and cook for 1 minute, stirring constantly.",
    "Add the Branston pickle, chicken stock, and brown sugar to the pot and stir to combine.",
    "Return the chicken to the pot and bring the mixture to a simmer.",
    "Transfer the pot to the preheated oven and roast for 20-25 minutes, or until the chicken is cooked through and the vegetables are tender.",
    "While the chicken is cooking, heat 2 tablespoons of olive oil in a small skillet over medium heat.",
    "Add the chopped pecans and cook until fragrant and lightly browned, about 2-3 minutes.",
    "Remove the pot from the oven and sprinkle the toasted pecans and fresh cilantro over the top.",
    "Serve the Roasted Kissed Jamaican Pickle Tagine hot, garnished with additional fresh cilantro and toasted pecans if desired."
  ],
